  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigated the feasibility of the novel modular mobile health (mHealth) for&#xD;
      personalized rehabilitation and explored the participants' satisfaction and app data during&#xD;
      treatment of breast cancer.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is prospective, feasible, parallel study in post-operative patients with breast cancer&#xD;
      and during treatment. Disability of Arm, Shoulder, Hands (DASH), Physical activity data&#xD;
      (IPAQ-SF), Physical measurement such as hand grip strength, body mass index (BMI), muscle&#xD;
      mass, and differences in arm circumference, PRO-CTCAE, Distress Thermometer, needs and&#xD;
      satisfaction in app, personal health record of app (exercise, daily step count, etc.) Measure&#xD;
      will be evaluated on 1-month, 2-month, 4-month, 6-month, 9-month, and 12-month after POD.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
